description:
Rewrite client/src/debug.ts to support Wine-style category-based logging.

## Changes needed

### 1. Parse debug string
```typescript
function parseDebugConfig(value: string): { enabledCategories: Set<string>, disabledCategories: Set<string>, allEnabled: boolean } {
  // Parse "+all,-mouse,+pane" format
  // Handle bare "true" for backward compat
}
```

### 2. Track category state
```typescript
let enabledCategories = new Set<string>();
let disabledCategories = new Set<string>();
let allEnabled = false;

function isCategoryEnabled(category: string): boolean {
  if (disabledCategories.has(category)) return false;
  if (enabledCategories.has(category)) return true;
  return allEnabled;
}
```

### 3. Category-scoped logger factory
```typescript
export function category(name: string) {
  return {
    log: (...args: unknown[]) => {
      if (isCategoryEnabled(name)) console.log(`[dullahan:${name}]`, ...args);
    },
    warn: (...args: unknown[]) => {
      if (isCategoryEnabled(name)) console.warn(`[dullahan:${name}]`, ...args);
    },
    error: (...args: unknown[]) => {
      // Always log errors
      console.error(`[dullahan:${name}]`, ...args);
    },
  };
}
```

### 4. Backward compatibility
- `?debug` (no value) â†’ `+all`
- `?debug=true` â†’ `+all`
- Keep existing `debug.log()` working (treat as uncategorized or 'misc')

### 5. Runtime API
```typescript
export function setCategories(config: string): void;
export function getCategories(): string;
export function listCategories(): string[]; // List all known categories
```

## Testing
- `?debug=+all` - everything logs
- `?debug=+mouse` - only mouse logs
- `?debug=+all,-mouse` - everything except mouse
- `?debug=-all,+mouse,+keyboard` - only mouse and keyboard
- `?debug` - backward compat, enables all

Modify KeyboardHandler to check keybinds before sending to server.

**Current flow:**
```
KeyboardEvent â†’ KeyboardHandler â†’ WebSocket â†’ Server â†’ PTY
```

**New flow:**
```
KeyboardEvent â†’ KeyboardHandler â†’ check keybinds
  â”œâ”€ match? â†’ execute action (don't send to server)
  â””â”€ no match? â†’ WebSocket â†’ Server â†’ PTY
```

**Implementation:**
```typescript
class KeyboardHandler {
  private keybinds: Map<string, TerminalAction>;

  setKeybinds(bindings: Array<{keybind: Keybind, action: TerminalAction}>): void;

  private handleKeyDown(e: KeyboardEvent): void {
    const action = this.matchKeybind(e);
    if (action) {
      e.preventDefault();
      this.executeAction(action);
    } else {
      this.sendToServer(e);
    }
  }
}
```

**Depends on:**
- du-9vm (action types)
- du-73i (keybind parser)
